$string['modguidesubmissions'] = '<h5>Submissions</h5><p>You must remain within any word or size limits set for your assessment. Exceeding such limits will result in being penalised according to the Academic Regulations for Taught Provision.</p><p>Electronic submissions will normally be through Moodle, although may use linked tools such as an ePortfolio or Video tool.<br>The standard maximum size for file uploads is 50Mb - your assessment brief will provide details if this has been altered to allow larger submissions (eg. large Media files).<br>You should use the following convention to name your files: <em>Bloggs_J_ s0123456_XX101_A1</em> (for example, Joe Bloggs –student number s0123456 – submitting a file for XX101 assessment task 1).<br>In most cases any relevant file format may be accepted, however, please pay attention to any specific requirements detailed in the Assignment Brief. PDF format is highly recommended for text based submissions, particularly those requiring detailed formatting.</p>';
$string['modguidefeedback'] = '<h5>Feedback</h5><p>You will receive a mark and feedback for each piece of coursework. This will normally be 20 working days after the due date - the expected return date is published in your module guide and on the assessment point itself.<br>
<strong>NOTE: Your initial grades on Moodle are provisional and subject to Exam Board ratification. Final agreed grades are always found as part of your Student Record transcript.</strong><br>
If there is anything that you do not understand about the feedback, please make an appointment to discuss with the Module Tutor. Your assignments and feedback will also be available to your personal tutor, who as part of the meeting each semester will check your understanding of feedback, and help you identify areas and strategies for improvement.</p>';
$string['modguidealternative'] = '<h5>Disabled Students</h5><p>Alternative assessment arrangements may be made, where appropriate, for disabled students. However, these will only be implemented upon the advice of the Disability Advisor. Disabled students wishing to be considered for alternative assessment arrangements must give notification of the disability (with evidence) to the Disability Advisor by the published deadlines.</p>';
$string['modguideregulations'] = '<h5>University Regulations for Assessment</h5><p> All assessments are subject to the Academic Regulations for Taught Provision. These include regulations relating to Errors of Attribution and Assessment Offences. In exercising their judgement, Examiners may penalise any work where the standard of English, numeracy or presentation adversely affects the quality of the work, or where the work submitted exceeds the published size or time limits, or where the work fails to follow normal academic conventions for acknowledging sources.</p>';
